#Text=Tehachapi
#Text=Tehachapi is a city in Kern County , California at the top of the Tehachapi Mountains which separate the San Joaquin Valley from the Mojave Desert .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Tehachapi is unusually windy .

#Text=Two of the largest wind farms in the United States are located here : the Alta Wind Engergy Center , which as of 2013 was the largest wind farm in the United States , and the Tehachapi Pass Wind Farm , which in 2013 was the fifth largest wind farm .
#Text=See
#Text=BeeKay Theatre .
#Text=Do
#Text=Hiking .
#Text=There are lots of excellent trails and parks for outdoor activities .
#Text=The Pacific Crest Trail passes through Tehachapi along highway 58 .
#Text=Tehachapi Mountain Park .
#Text=Great park on the base of Tehachapi mountain , the highest mountain in nearby range .
#Text=A 3-mile trail will take you to the summit , almost 8,000 ft altitude .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Petra , 200 S Green St , ☏ +1661 822-1900 .
#Text=Mediterranean food .
#Text=Kohnen 's Country Bakery , 125 W Tehachapi Blvd D. 6AM – 6PM daily .
#Text=German bakery .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Stallion Springs Resort , 28681 Stallion Springs Dr , toll-free : +1-888-828-6745 .
#Text=An out-of-the-city , out-of-the-ordinary , quiet , friendly timeshare environment offering one and two bedroom luxury cottages with swimming and seasonal tennis and golf nearby .

#Text=Go next

#Text=Bakersfield - Nicknamed " the country music capital of the West Coast " , Bakersfield is the largest city in the southern San Joaquin Valley and is thus the best option for those seeking lodging , transportation , or other services .
#Text=Keene - Located west on Highway 58 , Keene is home to the Cesar E. Chavez National Monument , which contains the headquarters and grave site of the famous labor leader .

#Text=Another attraction is the Tehachapi Loop , which is located just outside of town and is a favorite of railroad fans around the world since the engineering wonder is one of the few places where a train can be seen passing over itself .

#Text=Mojave - East of Tehachapi on Highway 58 , Mojave is a hotbed of aerospace activity , with the Mojave Spaceport the headquarters of Scaled Composites , the first private company to launch a human into space .
#Text=Edwards Air Force base , a landing site for the space shuttle and a center for the development of experimental aircraft , is located adjacent to the town .
